title: Grateful Dead Live at The Matrix on 1966-12-01
lineage: Tascam DA-20 mkII>SB Audigy>SF 6.0>CD Wave>mkwACT>SHN>Sound Forge 11>Flac
description:
Set I
Minglewood Blues, Betty & Dupree, Next Time You See Me, I Know You Rider, Big Boss Man, One Kind Favor, Alice D. Millionaire, Me & My Uncle, Cream Puff War
Set II
You Don't Love Me, Beat It On Down The Line, It Hurts Me Too, On The Road Again, Look Over Yonder's Wall, My Own Fault, Down So Long, Cold Rain & Snow, Viola Lee Blues
Set III
Deep Elem Blues, There's Something On Your Mind, Big Boy Pete, Death Don't Have No Mercy, Lindy, Dancin' In The Streets, Me & My Uncle
Comment
"Merry-Go-Round Broke Down" Tuning after, Me & My Uncle - Other artist(s): Jerry Pond

reviews.review_text: Great Show with Lots of Fun Song Choices! My title says it all. Fun fact: Listen about half way through on One Kind Favor, Garcia basically recycles a turnaround lick from Minglewood. Enjoy!

WOOOOOOOOOO!!!!! If you listen to this show and do not enjoy it, then you are probably deaf. Or you listen to entirely too much Kelly Clarkson. Because this show is HOT! I usually put a list of highlights, but that is impossible for this show. EVERY song is a highlight!!! top 10 io games for 68, top 20 ALL TIME for me (if not top 10)!
